   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-a" mid="9" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="7"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>I wouldn't go far as calling it an ambition, but I would like to make a legendary heraldry someday.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-b" mid="11" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Being a world-saving hero.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-e" mid="12" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Finding a treasure.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-h" mid="13" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>I'll just follow whatever fate had laid for me.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="10"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>But to do that, I'll need extremely rare Plates and Jewel.<BR>What's your ambition?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-c" mid="25" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="14"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>A world-saving hero.<BR>But if it's you, {user_nick}, I think it will be more than possible. If you never lose courage and keep walking on the correct path, one day you'll realize that you've become that hero.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-d" mid="26" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="15"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>When that day comes, I will be able to proudly tell everyone that you were quite the noticeable person even when you were at Calderock.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_question mid="16"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>Then, I should treasure these moments with you also.<BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>(Heraldry Scholar Bailey looks at you with a warm gaze.)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-f" mid="27" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="17"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>What kind of treasure are you talking about? Hmm... during the days when many merchants from Saint Haven used to come here, I heard something about pirate's treasure.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-g" mid="28" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="18"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>It was a story about a group of pirates who went separated ways after not being able to find the treasure they hid last time.<BR>If I had the power and the knowledge, it would've been pretty fun going on an adventure to look for that treasure.<BR>Just like you! Haha.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-g" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_question mid="19"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>If you manage to find the treasure, please tell me the story about how you found it.<BR>I'll be waiting with expectations.<BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>(Heraldry Scholar Bailey looks at you with a warm gaze.)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-h" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-i" mid="29" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="20"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>What a refreshing answer... Well, it's a typical answer for an elf, but...<BR>I have my doubts on whether something like fate really exists.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-i" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-j" mid="30" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="21"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>Realizing that something was a fate... won't that occur when everything ends, whether you are human or an elf? Having to undergo through the trials and choice in life one realizes that "Ah, that was my fate."</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-j" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-k" mid="31" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="22"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>Then would that really be fate?<BR>Wouldn't that be just... trials of the past?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-k" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_question mid="23"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>I think about this sometimes when I look at Master Archer Adelynn. Of course, there are some aspects of elves' way of living that we could definitely learn from...<BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>(Heraldry Scholar Bailey looks confused and lost in thought.)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
